    "content": "nullSalesforce B2B Commerce for Visualforce\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Salesforce B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Get Started with B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Manage Storefront Details and Metadata\n Set Up Product Data for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Help Buyers Discover Products on Your Storefront\n Price and Sell Products for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Support Buyer Accounts for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Provide a Smooth Path to Purchase for Storefront Buyers\n Customize the Storefront User Experience\n Considerations for Storefront User Experience Customizations\n Configure the Default Storefront Pages\n Modify the Column Layout of a Storefront Page\n Add Widgets to Storefront Pages with Visualforce Components\n Manage the Storefront Header\n Show the Breadcrumb Widget\n Show the Category Tree Widget\n Show the Effective Account Selector\n Show the Feature Filtering Widget\n Show the Locale Switcher Widget\n Show the Mini Cart Widget\n Show the Quick Order Widget\n Show the Reorder Widget\n Show the Search Box Widget\n Show the Splash Widget\n Show Spotlight Products and Featured Products\n Considerations for Autocomplete Suggestions in Search Box and Quick...\n Customize Storefront Headings and Text with Page Labels\n Provide Intuitive Storefront Navigation with Menus\n Author Custom Content for a Storefront Page\n Style Your Storefront with a Theme\n Extend the Default Storefront Pages\n Source Options for Storefront Media\n Allow Only One Country, Territory, or State in Address Picklists\n Strategize for Storefront Success\n Deliver Storefront Performance and Security\n Market Templates for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Solution Resources for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nVISUALFORCE B2B COMMERCE\nShow the Splash Widget\n\nCapture your buyers' attention with a series of large, prominently displayed images that can link to particular products, categories, or URLs. When you enable the Splash widget, promotions that you've enabled for the Splash location type automatically cycle through in a carousel or slideshow.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS\n\nSalesforce Compatibility\n\nSalesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience for Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer editions.\n\n\n\n\nB2B Commerce Compatibility\n\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Winter ’21 (version 4.13)\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Spring ’20 (version 4.12)\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Summer ’19 (version 4.11)\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Spring ’19 (version 4.10)\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Summer ’18 (version 4.9)\n\n\nUSER PERMISSIONS NEEDED\nTo create CC Promotion records:\tCreate on CC Promotions\nTo access CC Admin and change settings:\tAccess B2B Commerce for Visualforce Admin Settings permission set\nUSER EXPERIENCE COMPATIBILITY\nInterface\tBootstrap 3 or classic\nPages\tHome page only\nPage layouts\tAny page layout\nUser visibility\tLogged-in users and guest users (depending on your storefront's guest user access)\n\nThe Splash widget appears below the menu navigation bar, and provides controls and indicators for the buyer to cycle through the promotions.\n\nTo enable the Splash widget for your storefront, create the corresponding promotion records and update your storefront configuration settings.\n\nComplete the steps in Enable Promotions for Your Storefront.\nCreate the promotions that you want to show in the Splash widget.\nFor help with adding promotion images and creating promotion records, review the information in Best Practices When Creating Promotions for Your Storefront.\nWhen you create promotion records, be sure to set the following values:\nPROMOTION FIELD\tVALUE\nLocation Type\tSplash\nPage Location\tLanding Page\nOptionally, link each promotion in the widget to a product, category, or custom URL.\nLink a Promotion to a Category\nLink a Promotion to a Product\nLink a Promotion to a Custom URL\nUpdate your storefront configuration settings.\nOn the CC Admin tab in your org, select your storefront (1).\nIn the Storefront Settings menu, select Configuration Settings (2).\nFrom the Module picklist, select Splash (3).\nFind the Enabled configuration (4), and make sure that its value is TRUE (5).\nTIP\nIf the value is FALSE, click Override in the Action column. Enter TRUE for Value, and click Create.\nIf the configuration doesn't exist, click New , enter the following values in the New Page Setting window, and click Create.\nFIELD\tVALUE\nModule\tSplash\nConfiguration\tEnabled\nPage\tHP\nValue\tTRUE\nNOTE\nThe other configurations of the Splash module—Home Page Top, Page Include Name, and Use Page Include—define legacy functionality.\nTo customize the default Splash widget functionality in new implementations, extend the default cc_SplashRD.component Visualforce component.\nBuild and activate a new configuration cache.\nSEE ALSO\nSet Up Promotions for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\nCreate a Gross Layout Override\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
